{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775883004047,"sessionID":"ses_2851ffec2ffeiksYiHePqod4EM","part":{"id":"prt_d7ae0233d0017N06RwDHLhm8fc","messageID":"msg_d7ae01583001YBagLH7jddR39w","sessionID":"ses_2851ffec2ffeiksYiHePqod4EM","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_b97be746c5334c7cbf457596","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-036/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-036/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-036: Dify 插件集成 — Design/设计说明\n2: \n3: ## 1. 架构 (Architecture)\n4: \n5: ### 1.1 定位 (Purpose/Positioning)\n6: \n7: <!-- TODO: Describe the purpose and positioning of this change -->\n8: \n9: ### 1.2 目录结构 (Directory Layout)\n10: \n11: **当前状态 (Before):**\n12: \n13: ```\n14: <!-- TODO: Current directory structure -->\n15: ```\n16: \n17: **目标状态 (After):**\n18: \n19: ```\n20: <!-- TODO: Target directory structure -->\n21: ```\n22: \n23: ### 1.3 依赖关系 (Dependencies)\n24: \n25: <!-- TODO: Describe dependencies -->\n26: \n27: ---\n28: \n29: ## 2. 数据结构 (Data Structures)\n30: \n31: <!-- TODO: Describe data structures -->\n32: \n33: ---\n34: \n35: ## 3. API 契约 (API Contracts)\n36: \n37: <!-- TODO: Describe API contracts -->\n38: \n39: ---\n40: \n41: ## 4. 错误处理 (Error Handling)\n42: \n43: <!-- TODO: Describe error handling strategy -->\n44: \n45: ---\n46: \n47: ## 5. 测试策略 (Testing Strategy)\n48: \n49: <!-- TODO: Describe testing strategy -->\n50: \n51: ---\n52: \n53: ## 6. 实现步骤 (Implementation Steps)\n54: \n55: <!-- TODO: Describe implementation phases -->\n56: \n57: ---\n58: \n59: ## 7. 后续变更 (Follow-up Changes)\n60: \n61: <!-- TODO: Describe follow-up changes -->\n\n(End of file - total 61 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-036: Dify 插件集成 — Design/设计说明\n\n## 1. 架构 (Architecture)\n\n### 1.1 定位 (Purpose/Positioning)\n\n<!-- TODO: Describe the purpose and positioning of this change -->\n\n### 1.2 目录结构 (Directory Layout)\n\n**当前状态 (Before):**\n\n```\n<!-- TODO: Current directory structure -->\n```\n\n**目标状态 (After):**\n\n```\n<!-- TODO: Target directory structure -->","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-036/design.md","time":{"start":1775883004024,"end":1775883004045}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775883005129,"sessionID":"ses_2851ffec2ffeiksYiHePqod4EM","part":{"id":"prt_d7ae028fb00164XKmNtJugO4Bv","messageID":"msg_d7ae01583001YBagLH7jddR39w","sessionID":"ses_2851ffec2ffeiksYiHePqod4EM","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_d20b8cbb0f43417d9b7a4fde","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-036/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-036/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-036: Dify 插件集成 — Delta Spec\n2: \n3: ## Context\n4: \n5: - **Module:** `integrations`\n6: - **Language:** Python\n7: - **Size:** M\n8: - **Base specs:** `integrations/design.md`, `integrations/spec.md`, `python-sdk/design.md`, `python-sdk/spec.md`\n9: \n10: ## Scope\n11: \n12: This delta spec covers the AgentCube Dify plugin integration — plugin bootstrap, manifest structure, provider descriptor, tool schema, credential validation, tool invocation, execution delegation to `agentcube.CodeInterpreterClient`, and plugin dependency pins. It also covers the PCAP analyzer example application — FastAPI service, LangChain/LangGraph agent composition, sandbox orchestration via `SandboxRunner`, container image, and Kubernetes deployment.\n13: \n14: ---\n15: \n16: ## Dify Plugin Bootstrap\n17: \n18: ### Requirement: Plugin process entrypoint\n19: \n20: The system SHALL expose a `main.py` that runs the Dify plugin framework with a configured maximum request timeout.\n21: \n22: #### Scenario: Plugin runs with timeout configuration\n23: - **GIVEN** `main.py` is executed by the Dify plugin runtime\n24: - **WHEN** the module loads\n25: - **THEN** it SHALL execute `Plugin(DifyPluginEnv(MAX_REQUEST_TIMEOUT=120)).run()` and block until the host stops it\n26: \n27: #### Scenario: MAX_REQUEST_TIMEOUT value\n28: - **GIVEN** the `DifyPluginEnv` is constructed\n29: - **WHEN** the timeout parameter is inspected\n30: - **THEN** `MAX_REQUEST_TIMEOUT` SHALL be `120` (seconds)\n31: \n32: ---\n33: \n34: ## Plugin Manifest\n35: \n36: ### Requirement: Root manifest.yaml structure\n37: \n38: The system SHALL ship a `manifest.yaml` at the plugin root declaring all required metadata fields for Dify to load and execute the plugin.\n39: \n40: #### Scenario: Top-level identity fields\n41: - **GIVEN** `manifest.yaml` is parsed\n42: - **WHEN** the top-level keys are inspected\n43: - **THEN** it SHALL include `version: \"0.0.2\"`, `type: \"plugin\"`, `author: \"volcano-sh\"`, and `name: \"agentcube\"`\n44: \n45: #### Scenario: Multilingual label\n46: - **GIVEN** the `label` field in the manifest\n47: - **WHEN** it is parsed\n48: - **THEN** it SHALL be a map with keys `en_US`, `ja_JP`, `zh_Hans`, `pt_BR`, each mapping to `\"Agentcube\"`\n49: \n50: #### Scenario: Multilingual description\n51: - **GIVEN** the `description` field in the manifest\n52: - **WHEN** it is parsed\n53: - **THEN** it SHALL be a multilingual map containing localized strings for AgentCube description\n54: \n55: #### Scenario: Icon fields\n56: - **GIVEN** the manifest icon configuration\n57: - **WHEN** it is parsed\n58: - **THEN** `icon` SHALL be `\"icon.png\"` and `icon_dark` SHALL be `\"icon-dark.png\"`\n59: \n60: #### Scenario: Resource permissions\n61: - **GIVEN** the `resource` field in the manifest\n62: - **WHEN** it is parsed\n63: - **THEN** it SHALL include `memory` and a `permission` subtree with flags and sizes for `tool`, `model`, `endpoint`, `app`, and `storage`\n64: \n65: #### Scenario: Plugin tools registration\n66: - **GIVEN** the `plugins.tools` field\n67: - **WHEN** it is parsed\n68: - **THEN** it SHALL be a list containing `[provider/agentcube.yaml]`\n69: \n70: #### Scenario: Meta section\n71: - **GIVEN** the `meta` field in the manifest\n72: - **WHEN** it is parsed\n73: - **THEN** it SHALL include `version`, `arch` (list containing `amd64` and `arm64`), `runner` (map with `language: \"python\"`, `version: \"3.12\"`, `entrypoint: \"main\"`), and `minimum_dify_version: null`\n74: \n75: #### Scenario: Additional metadata fields\n76: - **GIVEN** the manifest root\n77: - **WHEN** optional fields are inspected\n78: - **THEN** it SHALL include `created_at`, `privacy`, `repo`, and `verified`\n79: \n80: ---\n81: \n82: ## Provider Descriptor\n83: \n84: ### Requirement: provider/agentcube.yaml structure\n85: \n86: The system SHALL define a tool provider YAML that identifies the Agentcube provider, lists its tools, and points to the Python implementation.\n87: \n88: #### Scenario: Provider identity\n89: - **GIVEN** `provider/agentcube.yaml` is parsed\n90: - **WHEN** the `identity` section is inspected\n91: - **THEN** it SHALL include `author`, `name`, `label` (multilingual map), `description` (multilingual map), and `icon`\n92: \n93: #### Scenario: Tools list\n94: - **GIVEN** the `tools` field in the provider descriptor\n95: - **WHEN** it is parsed\n96: - **THEN** it SHALL be a list containing `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml`\n97: \n98: #### Scenario: Python source pointer\n99: - **GIVEN** the `extra.python.source` field\n100: - **WHEN** it is parsed\n101: - **THEN** it SHALL be `\"provider/agentcube.py\"`\n102: \n103: #### Scenario: OAuth schema is commented out\n104: - **GIVEN** the provider descriptor file content\n105: - **WHEN** the file is read as text\n106: - **THEN** any `oauth_schema` block SHALL be present only as comments (not active YAML)\n107: \n108: ---\n109: \n110: ## Tool Parameter Schema\n111: \n112: ### Requirement: tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml schema\n113: \n114: The system SHALL declare a tool schema with connection endpoints, language selection, and code/command/session fields.\n115: \n116: #### Scenario: Tool identity\n117: - **GIVEN** the tool YAML `identity` section\n118: - **WHEN** it is parsed\n119: - **THEN** `identity.name` SHALL be `\"agentcube-code-interpreter\"`, `identity.author` SHALL be `\"agentcube\"`, and `label`/`description` SHALL include both `human` and `llm` string variants\n120: \n121: #### Scenario: Required string parameters\n122: - **GIVEN** the `parameters` list\n123: - **WHEN** parameters with `required: true` are filtered\n124: - **THEN** they SHALL include `router_url` (type: string, form: form) and `workload_manager_url` (type: string, form: form)\n125: \n126: #### Scenario: Optional language select\n127: - **GIVEN** the `language` parameter\n128: - **WHEN** it is parsed\n129: - **THEN** it SHALL have `type: select`, `required: false`, `form: llm`, and `options` SHALL be `[\"python\", \"javascript\", \"typescript\"]`\n130: \n131: #### Scenario: Optional code and command parameters\n132: - **GIVEN** the `parameters` list\n133: - **WHEN** optional parameters are inspected\n134: - **THEN** it SHALL include `code` (type: string), `command` (type: string), `session_id` (type: string), `session_reuse` (type: boolean), and `code_interpreter_id` (type: string), all with `required: false` and `form: llm`\n135: \n136: #### Scenario: Parameter documentation\n137: - **GIVEN** each parameter entry\n138: - **WHEN** it is parsed\n139: - **THEN** it SHALL include `name`, `type`, `required`, `label`, `human_description`, `llm_description`, and `form`\n140: \n141: #### Scenario: Python source pointer\n142: - **GIVEN** the tool YAML `extra.python.source` field\n143: - **WHEN** it is parsed\n144: - **THEN** it SHALL be `\"tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py\"`\n145: \n146: ---\n147: \n148: ## Provider Implementation\n149: \n150: ### Requirement: AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider class\n151: \n152: The system SHALL implement a Dify `ToolProvider` subclass with credential validation.\n153: \n154: #### Scenario: Class inheritance\n155: - **GIVEN** `provider/agentcube.py`\n156: - **WHEN** the class definition is inspected\n157: - **THEN** `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider` SHALL inherit from `dify_plugin.ToolProvider`\n158: \n159: #### Scenario: Import of validation error\n160: - **GIVEN** the imports in `provider/agentcube.py`\n161: - **WHEN** the file is parsed\n162: - **THEN** it SHALL import `ToolProviderCredentialValidationError` from `dify_plugin.errors.tool`\n163: \n164: #### Scenario: _validate_credentials method signature\n165: - **GIVEN** the provider class\n166: - **WHEN** `_validate_credentials` is inspected\n167: - **THEN** it SHALL accept `self` and `credentials: dict[str, Any]` and return `None`\n168: \n169: #### Scenario: Validation error propagation\n170: - **GIVEN** `_validate_credentials` encounters an error condition\n171: - **WHEN** an exception is caught\n172: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `ToolProviderCredentialValidationError(str(e))` with the exception message\n173: \n174: #### Scenario: Successful validation returns quietly\n175: - **GIVEN** credentials that pass validation\n176: - **WHEN** `_validate_credentials` runs\n177: - **THEN** the method SHALL return `None` without raising\n178: \n179: ---\n180: \n181: ## Tool Implementation\n182: \n183: ### Requirement: AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool class\n184: \n185: The system SHALL implement a Dify `Tool` subclass that delegates execution to `agentcube.CodeInterpreterClient` and returns JSON messages.\n186: \n187: #### Scenario: Class inheritance and imports\n188: - **GIVEN** `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py`\n189: - **WHEN** the file is parsed\n190: - **THEN** it SHALL import `Tool` from `dify_plugin`, `ToolInvokeMessage` from `dify_plugin.entities.tool`, and `CodeInterpreterClient` from `agentcube`\n191: \n192: #### Scenario: _invoke delegates to execute\n193: - **GIVEN** `_invoke(self, tool_parameters: dict[str, Any])` is called\n194: - **WHEN** the method executes\n195: - **THEN** it SHALL call `self.execute(**tool_parameters)` and yield `self.create_json_message(result)`\n196: \n197: #### Scenario: _invoke returns a generator\n198: - **GIVEN** the `_invoke` method signature\n199: - **WHEN** the return type is inspected\n200: - **THEN** it SHALL be `Generator[ToolInvokeMessage]`\n201: \n202: ### Requirement: execute method signature\n203: \n204: The system SHALL implement `execute` with parameters matching the tool schema, delegating to the AgentCube SDK.\n205: \n206: #### Scenario: execute parameter defaults\n207: - **GIVEN** the `execute` method signature\n208: - **WHEN** default values are inspected\n209: - **THEN** `language` SHALL default to `\"python\"` and `session_reuse` SHALL default to `False`\n210: \n211: #### Scenario: execute accepts all tool parameters\n212: - **GIVEN** the `execute` method\n213: - **WHEN** its parameters are inspected\n214: - **THEN** it SHALL accept `router_url`, `workload_manager_url`, `language`, `code_interpreter_id`, `session_id`, `code`, `command`, `session_reuse`, and `**kwargs`\n215: \n216: #### Scenario: execute delegates to CodeInterpreterClient\n217: - **GIVEN** valid `router_url` and `workload_manager_url`\n218: - **WHEN** `execute` is called with `code` or `command`\n219: - **THEN** it SHALL instantiate or use `CodeInterpreterClient` from `agentcube` to perform the corresponding remote operation\n220: \n221: #### Scenario: execute returns JSON-serializable result\n222: - **GIVEN** `execute` completes successfully\n223: - **WHEN** the return value is inspected\n224: - **THEN** it SHALL be a JSON-serializable object suitable for `create_json_message`\n225: \n226: ---\n227: \n228: ## Plugin Dependencies\n229: \n230: ### Requirement: requirements.txt pins\n231: \n232: The system SHALL pin compatible versions of `dify-plugin` and `agentcube-sdk`.\n233: \n234: #### Scenario: dify-plugin version bounds\n235: - **GIVEN** `integrations/dify-plugin/requirements.txt`\n236: - **WHEN** dependencies are parsed\n237: - **THEN** `dify-plugin` SHALL satisfy `>=0.4.2,<0.5.0`\n238: \n239: #### Scenario: agentcube-sdk version lower bound\n240: - **GIVEN** `integrations/dify-plugin/requirements.txt`\n241: - **WHEN** dependencies are parsed\n242: - **THEN** `agentcube-sdk` SHALL satisfy `>=0.0.10`\n243: \n244: ---\n245: \n246: ## PCAP Analyzer FastAPI Service\n247: \n248: ### Requirement: Application startup and configuration\n249: \n250: The system SHALL provide a FastAPI application that validates OpenAI-compatible configuration at startup.\n251: \n252: #### Scenario: API key required at startup\n253: - **GIVEN** the environment lacks `OPENAI_API_KEY` (or equivalent)\n254: - **WHEN** `on_startup()` runs\n255: - **THEN** the application SHALL fail startup rather than serve requests without credentials\n256: \n257: #### Scenario: API base URL default\n258: - **GIVEN** `OPENAI_API_BASE` is not set\n259: - **WHEN** the application reads configuration\n260: - **THEN** `API_BASE_URL` SHALL default to `\"https://api.siliconflow.cn/v1\"`\n261: \n262: #### Scenario: Model name default\n263: - **GIVEN** `OPENAI_MODEL` is not set\n264: - **WHEN** the application reads configuration\n265: - **THEN** `MODEL_NAME` SHALL default to `\"Qwen/QwQ-32B\"`\n266: \n267: #### Scenario: Code interpreter name default\n268: - **GIVEN** `CODEINTERPRETER_NAME` is not set\n269: - **WHEN** the application reads configuration\n270: - **THEN** it SHALL default to `\"my-interpreter\"`\n271: \n272: #### Scenario: Sandbox namespace default\n273: - **GIVEN** `SANDBOX_NAMESPACE` is not set\n274: - **WHEN** the application reads configuration\n275: - **THEN** it SHALL default to `\"default\"`\n276: \n277: #### Scenario: Sandbox warmup default\n278: - **GIVEN** `SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC` is not set\n279: - **WHEN** the application reads configuration\n280: - **THEN** it SHALL default to `5`\n281: \n282: #### Scenario: Server binding\n283: - **GIVEN** the application constants\n284: - **WHEN** server configuration is inspected\n285: - **THEN** `SERVER_HOST` SHALL be `\"0.0.0.0\"`, `SERVER_PORT` SHALL be `8000`, and `SERVER_RELOAD` SHALL be `True`\n286: \n287: ### Requirement: Agent composition\n288: \n289: The system SHALL compose LangChain/LangGraph agents for planning, execution, and reporting.\n290: \n291: #### Scenario: ReAct agent builder\n292: - **GIVEN** an LLM instance and system prompt\n293: - **WHEN** `build_react_agent(llm, system_prompt)` is called\n294: - **THEN** it SHALL return a ReAct agent using `langgraph.prebuilt.create_react_agent`\n295: \n296: #### Scenario: Planner agent builder\n297: - **GIVEN** an LLM instance\n298: - **WHEN** `build_planner_agent(llm)` is called\n299: - **THEN** it SHALL return an agent configured for script planning\n300: \n301: #### Scenario: Reporter agent builder\n302: - **GIVEN** an LLM instance\n303: - **WHEN** `build_reporter_agent(llm)` is called\n304: - **THEN** it SHALL return an agent configured for report generation\n305: \n306: #### Scenario: ReAct agent invocation\n307: - **GIVEN** a built ReAct agent and user text\n308: - **WHEN** `invoke_react_agent(agent, user_text)` is called\n309: - **THEN** it SHALL return the agent's response as a string\n310: \n311: ### Requirement: Analysis orchestration\n312: \n313: The system SHALL orchestrate PCAP analysis through planning, execution with retries, and reporting.\n314: \n315: #### Scenario: Plan script generation\n316: - **GIVEN** a planner agent and a local PCAP path\n317: - **WHEN** `_plan_script(agent, pcap_local_path)` is called\n318: - **THEN** it SHALL return a script string generated by the planner agent\n319: \n320: #### Scenario: Script repair\n321: - **GIVEN** a reporter agent, a previous script, and execution results\n322: - **WHEN** `_repair_script(agent, prev_script, results)` is called\n323: - **THEN** it SHALL return a revised script string\n324: \n325: #### Scenario: Single execution in sandbox\n326: - **GIVEN** a `SandboxRunner`, local PCAP path, and script\n327: - **WHEN** `_execute_once_in_runner(runner, pcap_local_path, script)` is called\n328: - **THEN** it SHALL upload the PCAP to the sandbox, execute the script, and return a list of result dicts\n329: \n330: #### Scenario: Analysis with retries\n331: - **GIVEN** analysis parameters and `max_retries=2`\n332: - **WHEN** `_analyze_with_retries(...)` is called\n333: - **THEN** it SHALL attempt planning, execution, and repair up to `max_retries` times, returning aggregated results\n334: \n335: #### Scenario: Report generation\n336: - **GIVEN** a reporter agent and execution results\n337: - **WHEN** `_report(agent, results)` is called\n338: - **THEN** it SHALL return a report string\n339: \n340: ### Requirement: Analyze endpoint\n341: \n342: The system SHALL expose `POST /analyze` accepting PCAP file uploads or paths.\n343: \n344: #### Scenario: Endpoint accepts file upload\n345: - **GIVEN** a running service with valid LLM configuration\n346: - **WHEN** `POST /analyze` is called with `pcap_file` as `UploadFile`\n347: - **THEN** the handler SHALL process the file and return `AnalyzeResponse(script, results, report)`\n348: \n349: #### Scenario: Endpoint accepts file path\n350: - **GIVEN** a running service\n351: - **WHEN** `POST /analyze` is called with `pcap_path` as form field\n352: - **THEN** the handler SHALL process the file at the given path and return `AnalyzeResponse`\n353: \n354: #### Scenario: Response model structure\n355: - **GIVEN** `AnalyzeResponse` is defined\n356: - **WHEN** the model fields are inspected\n357: - **THEN** it SHALL have `script: str`, `results: List[Dict[str, Any]]`, and `report: str`\n358: \n359: #### Scenario: Endpoint signature\n360: - **GIVEN** the endpoint definition\n361: - **WHEN** the function signature is inspected\n362: - **THEN** it SHALL be `async def analyze_endpoint(pcap_file: UploadFile = File(None), pcap_path: str = Form(None))` with `response_model=AnalyzeResponse`\n363: \n364: ---\n365: \n366: ## SandboxRunner\n367: \n368: ### Requirement: SandboxRunner constructor\n369: \n370: The system SHALL construct a `SandboxRunner` with interpreter name, namespace, and warmup duration.\n371: \n372: #### Scenario: Default constructor parameters\n373: - **GIVEN** `SandboxRunner()` is called with no arguments\n374: - **WHEN** the instance is created\n375: - **THEN** `name` SHALL be `\"my-interpreter\"`, `namespace` SHALL be `\"default\"`, and `warmup_sec` SHALL be `5`\n376: \n377: #### Scenario: Custom constructor parameters\n378: - **GIVEN** `SandboxRunner(name=\"custom\", namespace=\"prod\", warmup_sec=10)`\n379: - **WHEN** the instance is created\n380: - **THEN** the instance fields SHALL reflect the provided values\n381: \n382: ### Requirement: SandboxRunner file operations\n383: \n384: The system SHALL provide `upload_file` and `upload_bytes` for staging artifacts in the sandbox.\n385: \n386: #### Scenario: upload_file stages local file\n387: - **GIVEN** a `SandboxRunner` instance and local/remote paths\n388: - **WHEN** `upload_file(local_path, remote_path)` is called\n389: - **THEN** it SHALL upload the file from `local_path` to `remote_path` in the sandbox and return `True` on success\n390: \n391: #### Scenario: upload_bytes stages byte content\n392: - **GIVEN** a `SandboxRunner` instance, byte data, and remote path\n393: - **WHEN** `upload_bytes(data, remote_path)` is called\n394: - **THEN** it SHALL upload the bytes to `remote_path` in the sandbox and return `True` on success\n395: \n396: ### Requirement: SandboxRunner command execution\n397: \n398: The system SHALL execute commands in the remote sandbox context.\n399: \n400: #### Scenario: run executes command\n401: - **GIVEN** a `SandboxRunner` and a shell command string\n402: - **WHEN** `run(command)` is called\n403: - **THEN** it SHALL execute the command in the sandbox and return a `Dict[str, Any]` with structured results\n404: \n405: ### Requirement: SandboxRunner lifecycle\n406: \n407: The system SHALL provide `stop` for cleanup.\n408: \n409: #### Scenario: stop releases resources\n410: - **GIVEN** a running `SandboxRunner`\n411: - **WHEN** `stop()` is called\n412: - **THEN** it SHALL release sandbox resources and perform cleanup\n413: \n414: ---\n415: \n416: ## PCAP Analyzer Container Image\n417: \n418: ### Requirement: Dockerfile structure\n419: \n420: The system SHALL build a container image that installs dependencies with `uv`, vendors the `agentcube` SDK, and starts the FastAPI app.\n421: \n422: #### Scenario: Base image\n423: - **GIVEN** the `Dockerfile`\n424: - **WHEN** the `FROM` instruction is inspected\n425: - **THEN** it SHALL use `ghcr.io/astral-sh/uv:python3.12-bookworm-slim`\n426: \n427: #### Scenario: Dependency installation\n428: - **GIVEN** the Dockerfile build steps\n429: - **WHEN** the installation commands are inspected\n430: - **THEN** it SHALL run `uv venv` and `uv pip install -r requirements.txt`\n431: \n432: #### Scenario: AgentCube SDK vendoring\n433: - **GIVEN** the Dockerfile copy instructions\n434: - **WHEN** the file copies are inspected\n435: - **THEN** it SHALL copy `sdk-python/agentcube` to `./agentcube/`\n436: \n437: #### Scenario: Application copy\n438: - **GIVEN** the Dockerfile copy instructions\n439: - **WHEN** the application copy is inspected\n440: - **THEN** it SHALL copy `pcap_analyzer.py` to `./`\n441: \n442: #### Scenario: PYTHONPATH and port\n443: - **GIVEN** the Dockerfile environment and exposure\n444: - **WHEN** they are inspected\n445: - **THEN** `PYTHONPATH` SHALL be `\"/app\"` and `EXPOSE 8000` SHALL be present\n446: \n447: #### Scenario: Default command\n448: - **GIVEN** the Dockerfile `CMD` instruction\n449: - **WHEN** it is inspected\n450: - **THEN** it SHALL be `[\"uv\", \"run\", \"pcap_analyzer.py\"]`\n451: \n452: ---\n453: \n454: ## PCAP Analyzer Kubernetes Deployment\n455: \n456: ### Requirement: Deployment manifest structure\n457: \n458: The system SHALL supply a K8s `Deployment` manifest for the analyzer.\n459: \n460: #### Scenario: Deployment metadata\n461: - **GIVEN** `deployment.yaml` is parsed\n462: - **WHEN** the Deployment metadata is inspected\n463: - **THEN** the name SHALL be `\"pcap-analyzer\"` and namespace SHALL be `\"default\"`\n464: \n465: #### Scenario: Container image and pull policy\n466: - **GIVEN** the container spec\n467: - **WHEN** image configuration is inspected\n468: - **THEN** `image` SHALL be `\"pcap-analyzer:latest\"` and `imagePullPolicy` SHALL be `\"IfNotPresent\"`\n469: \n470: #### Scenario: Container port\n471: - **GIVEN** the container ports\n472: - **WHEN** they are inspected\n473: - **THEN** port `8000` TCP SHALL be exposed\n474: \n475: #### Scenario: Resource requests\n476: - **GIVEN** the container resources\n477: - **WHEN** requests are inspected\n478: - **THEN** `cpu` SHALL be `\"200m\"` and `memory` SHALL be `\"100Mi\"`\n479: \n480: #### Scenario: Resource limits\n481: - **GIVEN** the container resources\n482: - **WHEN** limits are inspected\n483: - **THEN** `cpu` SHALL be `\"1\"` and `memory` SHALL be `\"1Gi\"`\n484: \n485: #### Scenario: OPENAI_API_KEY from Secret\n486: - **GIVEN** the container environment variables\n487: - **WHEN** `OPENAI_API_KEY` env is inspected\n488: - **THEN** it SHALL reference Secret `pcap-analyzer-secrets` with key `openai-api-key`\n489: \n490: #### Scenario: Plain environment variables\n491: - **GIVEN** the container environment variables\n492: - **WHEN** they are inspected\n493: - **THEN** `OPENAI_API_BASE`, `OPENAI_MODEL`, `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`, `ROUTER_URL`, `CODEINTERPRETER_NAME`, `SANDBOX_NAMESPACE`, and `SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC` SHALL be set as plain env values\n494: \n495: #### Scenario: Container command\n496: - **GIVEN** the container command/args\n497: - **WHEN** they are inspected\n498: - **THEN** `command` SHALL be `[\"uv\"]` and `args` SHALL be `[\"run\", \"pcap_analyzer.py\"]`\n499: \n500: ---\n501: \n502: ## PCAP Analyzer Python Dependencies\n503: \n504: ### Requirement: example/pcap-analyzer/requirements.txt\n505: \n506: The system SHALL pin specific versions for the FastAPI, LangChain/LangGraph, and related dependencies.\n507: \n508: #### Scenario: FastAPI and uvicorn pins\n509: - **GIVEN** `example/pcap-analyzer/requirements.txt`\n510: - **WHEN** the file is parsed\n511: - **THEN** it SHALL include `fastapi==0.120.0` and `uvicorn==0.38.0`\n512: \n513: #### Scenario: LangChain stack pins\n514: - **GIVEN** the requirements file\n515: - **WHEN** LangChain packages are inspected\n516: - **THEN** it SHALL include `langchain==1.0.2`, `langchain-classic==1.0.0`, `langchain-community==0.4.1`, `langchain-core==1.0.1`, `langchain-openai==1.0.1`, `langchain-text-splitters==1.0.0`, `langgraph==1.0.1`, `langgraph-checkpoint==3.0.0`, `langgraph-prebuilt==1.0.1`, `langgraph-sdk==0.2.9`, and `langsmith==0.4.38`\n517: \n518: #### Scenario: Additional dependencies\n519: - **GIVEN** the requirements file\n520: - **WHEN** remaining packages are inspected\n521: - **THEN** it SHALL include `paramiko==4.0.0` and `python-multipart==0.0.20`\n522: \n523: #### Scenario: agentcube not in requirements\n524: - **GIVEN** the requirements file content\n525: - **WHEN** the file is searched for `agentcube`\n526: - **THEN** it SHALL NOT be listed (the Dockerfile vendors it from the monorepo)\n527: \n528: ---\n529: \n530: ## File Changes\n531: \n532: | Action | File | Description |\n533: |--------|------|-------------|\n534: | Create | `integrations/dify-plugin/main.py` | Plugin entrypoint: `Plugin(DifyPluginEnv(MAX_REQUEST_TIMEOUT=120)).run()` |\n535: | Create | `integrations/dify-plugin/manifest.yaml` | Root plugin manifest with metadata, resources, meta, tools |\n536: | Create | `integrations/dify-plugin/provider/agentcube.yaml` | Tool provider descriptor with identity, tools, python source |\n537: | Create | `integrations/dify-plugin/provider/agentcube.py` | `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider` with `_validate_credentials` |\n538: | Create | `integrations/dify-plugin/tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml` | Tool parameter schema (router_url, workload_manager_url, language, code, command, session) |\n539: | Create | `integrations/dify-plugin/tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py` | `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool` with `_invoke` and `execute` |\n540: | Create | `integrations/dify-plugin/requirements.txt` | `dify-plugin>=0.4.2,<0.5.0` + `agentcube-sdk>=0.0.10` |\n541: | Create | `integrations/dify-plugin/GUIDE.md` | Plugin usage guide |\n542: | Create | `integrations/dify-plugin/README.md` | Plugin documentation |\n543: | Create | `integrations/dify-plugin/PRIVACY.md` | Privacy policy |\n544: | Create | `integrations/dify-plugin/.difyignore` | Dify ignore patterns |\n545: | Create | `example/pcap-analyzer/pcap_analyzer.py` | FastAPI app with agents, SandboxRunner, /analyze endpoint |\n546: | Create | `example/pcap-analyzer/requirements.txt` | Pinned FastAPI, LangChain, LangGraph, paramiko, python-multipart |\n547: | Create | `example/pcap-analyzer/Dockerfile` | uv-based image with vendored agentcube SDK |\n548: | Create | `example/pcap-analyzer/deployment.yaml` | K8s Deployment with secrets, env, resources |\n549: | Create | `example/pcap-analyzer/README.md` | PCAP analyzer documentation |\n550: \n551: ---\n552: \n553: ## Status\n554: \n555: - [ ] Spec review\n556: - [ ] Implementation\n557: - [ ] Verification\n\n(End of file - total 557 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-036: Dify 插件集成 — Delta Spec\n\n## Context\n\n- **Module:** `integrations`\n- **Language:** Python\n- **Size:** M\n- **Base specs:** `integrations/design.md`, `integrations/spec.md`, `python-sdk/design.md`, `python-sdk/spec.md`\n\n## Scope\n\nThis delta spec covers the AgentCube Dify plugin integration — plugin bootstrap, manifest structure, provider descriptor, tool schema, credential validation, tool invocation, execution delegation to `agentcube.CodeInterpreterClient`, and plugin dependency pins. It also covers the PCAP analyzer example application — FastAPI service, LangChain/LangGraph agent composition, sandbox orchestration via `SandboxRunner`, container image, and Kubernetes deployment.\n\n---\n\n## Dify Plugin Bootstrap\n\n### Requirement: Plugin process entrypoint\n\nThe system SHALL expose a `main.py` that runs the Dify plugin framework with a configured maximum request timeout.","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-036/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775883005118,"end":1775883005127}}}}
