{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775883008488,"sessionID":"ses_2851ffec2ffeiksYiHePqod4EM","part":{"id":"prt_d7ae03167001T6pyOajtK67SRv","messageID":"msg_d7ae01583001YBagLH7jddR39w","sessionID":"ses_2851ffec2ffeiksYiHePqod4EM","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_604991fcf4b5428cbe5d3fd9","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-036/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-036/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-036 — Dify 插件集成 — Tasks\n2: \n3: > **Module:** integrations\n4: > **Language:** Python\n5: > **Size:** M\n6: > **Precondition:** Stage ST-3 (Design) completed\n7: > **Reference:** `changes/AR-036/proposal.md`, `changes/AR-036/design.md`, `changes/AR-036/delta-spec.md`\n8: \n9: ---\n10: \n11: ## T-001: <!-- TODO: Task title -->\n12: \n13: - [ ] <!-- TODO: Task item -->\n14: \n15: **验收**:\n16: ```bash\n17: <!-- TODO: Verification command -->\n18: ```\n19: \n20: ---\n21: \n22: ## Dependency Graph\n23: \n24: ```\n25: <!-- TODO: Task dependency graph -->\n26: ```\n27: \n28: ## Parallelizable Groups\n29: \n30: | Group | Tasks | Prerequisites |\n31: |-------|-------|---------------|\n32: | <!-- TODO --> | <!-- TODO --> | <!-- TODO --> |\n33: \n34: ---\n35: \n36: ## Acceptance Criteria\n37: \n38: | # | Criterion | Command |\n39: |---|-----------|---------|\n40: | 1 | <!-- TODO --> | <!-- TODO --> |\n\n(End of file - total 40 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-036 — Dify 插件集成 — Tasks\n\n> **Module:** integrations\n> **Language:** Python\n> **Size:** M\n> **Precondition:** Stage ST-3 (Design) completed\n> **Reference:** `changes/AR-036/proposal.md`, `changes/AR-036/design.md`, `changes/AR-036/delta-spec.md`\n\n---\n\n## T-001: <!-- TODO: Task title -->\n\n- [ ] <!-- TODO: Task item -->\n\n**验收**:\n```bash\n<!-- TODO: Verification command -->\n```\n\n---","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-036/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775883008479,"end":1775883008487}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775883009761,"sessionID":"ses_2851ffec2ffeiksYiHePqod4EM","part":{"id":"prt_d7ae03b0e001QWawZhCyiShiWw","messageID":"msg_d7ae01583001YBagLH7jddR39w","sessionID":"ses_2851ffec2ffeiksYiHePqod4EM","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_b367205926fc4a04b1977a86","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/integrations/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/integrations/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Integrations Specification\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: Normative requirements for the AgentCube Dify plugin integration and the PCAP analyzer example that uses AgentCube code interpreters and Kubernetes sandboxes.\n6: \n7: ## Requirements\n8: \n9: ### Requirement: Dify plugin bootstrap and runtime\n10: \n11: The system SHALL expose a Dify-compatible Python plugin whose process entry runs the framework runner with a configured maximum request timeout.\n12: \n13: #### Scenario: Plugin process starts\n14: \n15: - **GIVEN** the plugin package is installed with compatible `dify-plugin` and `agentcube-sdk` versions\n16: - **WHEN** the platform starts the plugin using the manifest-declared entrypoint\n17: - **THEN** the plugin SHALL execute `main` which runs `Plugin(DifyPluginEnv(MAX_REQUEST_TIMEOUT=120)).run()` until the host stops it\n18: \n19: ---\n20: \n21: ### Requirement: Plugin manifest structure\n22: \n23: The system SHALL ship a root `manifest.yaml` declaring plugin metadata, tool provider registration, resource permissions, and runner metadata sufficient for Dify to load and execute the plugin.\n24: \n25: #### Scenario: Required manifest fields\n26: \n27: - **GIVEN** a valid plugin package root\n28: - **WHEN** the manifest is parsed by a Dify-compatible toolchain\n29: - **THEN** the manifest SHALL include `version`, `type: plugin`, `author`, `name`, `label` (multilingual map), `description` (multilingual), `icon`, `icon_dark`, `resource` (including `memory` and `permission` subtree), `plugins.tools` listing provider descriptors, and `meta` containing `version`, `arch`, `runner` (`language`, `version`, `entrypoint`), and `minimum_dify_version`\n30: \n31: #### Scenario: Tool provider wiring\n32: \n33: - **GIVEN** the manifest `plugins.tools` references the Agentcube provider descriptor\n34: - **WHEN** the plugin is loaded\n35: - **THEN** Dify SHALL resolve `provider/agentcube.yaml` and associate it with the Python module declared under `extra.python.source`\n36: \n37: ---\n38: \n39: ### Requirement: Provider descriptor structure\n40: \n41: The system SHALL define a tool provider YAML that identifies the provider, lists its tools, and points to the Python provider implementation.\n42: \n43: #### Scenario: Provider lists tools and entry module\n44: \n45: - **GIVEN** `provider/agentcube.yaml` is present\n46: - **WHEN** the integration runtime resolves the provider\n47: - **THEN** the descriptor SHALL include `identity` (author, name, multilingual label/description, icon), a `tools` list including `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml`, and `extra.python.source: provider/agentcube.py`\n48: \n49: ---\n50: \n51: ### Requirement: Tool parameter schema\n52: \n53: The system SHALL declare a tool schema for the code interpreter integration including connection endpoints, optional language selection, and code/command/session fields.\n54: \n55: #### Scenario: Declared parameters match remote APIs\n56: \n57: - **GIVEN** `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml`\n58: - **WHEN** an operator configures the tool in Dify\n59: - **THEN** the schema SHALL require string parameters `router_url` and `workload_manager_url`, SHALL offer optional `language` as a select among `python`, `javascript`, and `typescript`, and SHALL allow optional `code`, `command`, `session_id`, `session_reuse` (boolean), and `code_interpreter_id`, each documented for human and LLM-oriented forms\n60: \n61: ---\n62: \n63: ### Requirement: Tool provider credential validation\n64: \n65: The system SHALL implement credential validation on the tool provider class and SHALL surface validation failures using the Dify tool provider error type.\n66: \n67: #### Scenario: Invalid credentials are rejected\n68: \n69: - **GIVEN** an instance of `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider`\n70: - **WHEN** `_validate_credentials` encounters an error condition the implementer treats as invalid\n71: - **THEN** the provider SHALL raise `ToolProviderCredentialValidationError` with a string message derived from the failure\n72: \n73: #### Scenario: Successful validation completes quietly\n74: \n75: - **GIVEN** credentials that satisfy the provider’s validation rules\n76: - **WHEN** `_validate_credentials` runs\n77: - **THEN** the method SHALL return without raising\n78: \n79: ---\n80: \n81: ### Requirement: Tool invocation and JSON messaging\n82: \n83: The system SHALL implement the Agentcube code interpreter tool as a Dify `Tool` that delegates execution and returns structured JSON to the host.\n84: \n85: #### Scenario: Dify invokes the tool\n86: \n87: - **GIVEN** a configured tool invocation with parameters matching the schema\n88: - **WHEN** Dify calls `_invoke` on `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool`\n89: - **THEN** the tool SHALL call `execute(**tool_parameters)` and SHALL yield `create_json_message(result)` for the outcome\n90: \n91: ---\n92: \n93: ### Requirement: Tool execution API surface\n94: \n95: The system SHALL implement `execute` with parameters for router and workload manager URLs, optional language, session controls, and code or command execution, delegating to `agentcube.CodeInterpreterClient`.\n96: \n97: #### Scenario: Code or command runs against configured endpoints\n98: \n99: - **GIVEN** valid `router_url`, `workload_manager_url`, and optional `language` defaulting to `python`\n100: - **WHEN** the tool receives `code` and/or `command` with optional `session_id`, `session_reuse`, and `code_interpreter_id`\n101: - **THEN** the tool SHALL use the AgentCube Python SDK client to perform the corresponding remote operations and SHALL return a JSON-serializable result object suitable for `create_json_message`\n102: \n103: ---\n104: \n105: ### Requirement: Plugin Python dependencies\n106: \n107: The system SHALL pin compatible versions of `dify-plugin` and `agentcube-sdk` for reproducible installs.\n108: \n109: #### Scenario: Dependency bounds\n110: \n111: - **GIVEN** `integrations/dify-plugin/requirements.txt`\n112: - **WHEN** dependencies are installed in a clean environment\n113: - **THEN** installs SHALL satisfy `dify-plugin>=0.4.2,<0.5.0` and `agentcube-sdk>=0.0.10`\n114: \n115: ---\n116: \n117: ### Requirement: PCAP analyzer FastAPI service\n118: \n119: The system SHALL provide a FastAPI application that validates OpenAI-compatible configuration at startup, composes LangChain/LangGraph agents, and exposes an analysis endpoint for PCAP uploads.\n120: \n121: #### Scenario: Startup requires API key\n122: \n123: - **GIVEN** the process is started without a usable `OPENAI_API_KEY` (or equivalent configured API key)\n124: - **WHEN** the application completes startup hooks\n125: - **THEN** startup SHALL fail rather than serve requests without credentials\n126: \n127: #### Scenario: Analyze endpoint accepts PCAP input\n128: \n129: - **GIVEN** a running service with valid LLM configuration\n130: - **WHEN** a client calls `POST /analyze` with either an uploaded PCAP file or a `pcap_path` form field\n131: - **THEN** the handler SHALL return a body matching `AnalyzeResponse` including `script`, `results`, and `report`\n132: \n133: ---\n134: \n135: ### Requirement: PCAP analyzer configuration surface\n136: \n137: The system SHALL read runtime configuration from environment variables for the OpenAI-compatible API, model selection, and AgentCube sandbox parameters.\n138: \n139: #### Scenario: Defaults and overrides\n140: \n141: - **GIVEN** standard deployment environment variables\n142: - **WHEN** the service starts\n143: - **THEN** it SHALL use `OPENAI_API_BASE` defaulting to `https://api.siliconflow.cn/v1`, `OPENAI_MODEL` defaulting to `Qwen/QwQ-32B`, `CODEINTERPRETER_NAME` defaulting to `my-interpreter`, `SANDBOX_NAMESPACE` defaulting to `default`, and `SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC` defaulting to `5`, while binding HTTP to `0.0.0.0:8000` as defined in the application\n144: \n145: ---\n146: \n147: ### Requirement: PCAP analyzer sandbox integration\n148: \n149: The system SHALL orchestrate PCAP analysis by planning and repairing scripts, executing them inside an AgentCube-backed sandbox via `SandboxRunner`, and aggregating results through reporter agents.\n150: \n151: #### Scenario: Sandbox runner executes commands\n152: \n153: - **GIVEN** a `SandboxRunner` constructed with interpreter name, namespace, and warmup duration\n154: - **WHEN** analysis logic invokes `run` with a shell command\n155: - **THEN** the runner SHALL execute the command in the remote sandbox context and SHALL return structured execution results for downstream LLM steps\n156: \n157: #### Scenario: File staging uses runner uploads\n158: \n159: - **GIVEN** a local PCAP path or bytes to analyze\n160: - **WHEN** the orchestration needs the artifact inside the sandbox workspace\n161: - **THEN** the system SHALL use `upload_file` or `upload_bytes` on `SandboxRunner` before executing analysis commands\n162: \n163: ---\n164: \n165: ### Requirement: PCAP analyzer container image\n166: \n167: The system SHALL build a container image that installs Python dependencies with `uv`, vendors the in-repo `agentcube` SDK copy, sets `PYTHONPATH`, exposes port 8000, and starts the FastAPI app via `uv run`.\n168: \n169: #### Scenario: Image entrypoint\n170: \n171: - **GIVEN** the `example/pcap-analyzer/Dockerfile` build context\n172: - **WHEN** the container runs without overriding the command\n173: - **THEN** the default command SHALL be `uv run pcap_analyzer.py` with `PYTHONPATH=\"/app\"` and port `8000` exposed\n174: \n175: ---\n176: \n177: ### Requirement: PCAP analyzer Kubernetes deployment\n178: \n179: The system SHALL supply a `Deployment` manifest that runs the analyzer image with resource requests/limits and environment variables wired from a Secret and plain env for AgentCube and model endpoints.\n180: \n181: #### Scenario: Deployment wiring\n182: \n183: - **GIVEN** `example/pcap-analyzer/deployment.yaml` applied to the cluster\n184: - **WHEN** the workload becomes ready\n185: - **THEN** the pod SHALL run image `pcap-analyzer:latest` (pull `IfNotPresent`), listen on TCP 8000, request `cpu: 200m` / `memory: 100Mi` and limit `cpu: 1` / `memory: 1Gi`, mount `OPENAI_API_KEY` from Secret `pcap-analyzer-secrets` key `openai-api-key`, and set `OPENAI_API_BASE`, `OPENAI_MODEL`, `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`, `ROUTER_URL`, `CODEINTERPRETER_NAME`, `SANDBOX_NAMESPACE`, and `SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC` as container environment variables\n186: \n187: #### Scenario: Process launch in cluster\n188: \n189: - **GIVEN** the deployment’s container specification\n190: - **WHEN** Kubernetes starts the container\n191: - **THEN** the command SHALL be `uv` with arguments `run pcap_analyzer.py`, matching local Docker behavior\n\n(End of file - total 191 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Integrations Specification\n\n## Purpose\n\nNormative requirements for the AgentCube Dify plugin integration and the PCAP analyzer example that uses AgentCube code interpreters and Kubernetes sandboxes.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Dify plugin bootstrap and runtime\n\nThe system SHALL expose a Dify-compatible Python plugin whose process entry runs the framework runner with a configured maximum request timeout.\n\n#### Scenario: Plugin process starts\n\n- **GIVEN** the plugin package is installed with compatible `dify-plugin` and `agentcube-sdk` versions\n- **WHEN** the platform starts the plugin using the manifest-declared entrypoint\n- **THEN** the plugin SHALL execute `main` which runs `Plugin(DifyPluginEnv(MAX_REQUEST_TIMEOUT=120)).run()` until the host stops it\n\n---\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/integrations/spec.md","time":{"start":1775883009751,"end":1775883009759}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775883011093,"sessionID":"ses_2851ffec2ffeiksYiHePqod4EM","part":{"id":"prt_d7ae03f97001VdN8gRzsWKlsFu","messageID":"msg_d7ae01583001YBagLH7jddR39w","sessionID":"ses_2851ffec2ffeiksYiHePqod4EM","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_2bfb7d4d64424342b8c14e43","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/integrations/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/integrations/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube Integrations — Design\n2: \n3: Sources: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/integrations/dify-plugin/`, `/tmp/agentcube-ref/example/pcap-analyzer/`.\n4: \n5: ## Architecture Overview\n6: \n7: The integrations module bridges AgentCube with two external systems:\n8: \n9: 1. **Dify Plugin** — A Dify-compatible Python plugin that exposes AgentCube's Code Interpreter as a tool within the Dify AI application platform.\n10: 2. **PCAP Analyzer** — A standalone FastAPI service that demonstrates end-to-end usage of the AgentCube SDK for PCAP file analysis via LLM-planned sandbox execution.\n11: \n12: ```\n13: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n14: │                        Dify Platform                            │\n15: │  ┌──────────────┐   ┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐ │\n16: │  │  Dify Agent  │──▶│  AgentCube Dify Plugin                  │ │\n17: │  │  (LLM)       │   │  ┌───────────┐  ┌─────────────────────┐ │ │\n18: │  └──────────────┘   │  │ Provider  │─▶│ Tool: Code          │ │ │\n19: │                     │  │ (creds)   │  │ Interpreter         │ │ │\n20: │                     │  └───────────┘  └─────────┬───────────┘ │ │\n21: │                     └───────────────────────────┼─────────────┘ │\n22: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────┼───────────────┘\n23:                                                   │\n24: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────┼───────────────┐\n25: │                    AgentCube SDK               │               │\n26: │                     ┌──────────▼──────────┐    │               │\n27: │                     │ CodeInterpreterClient│    │               │\n28: │                     │  ┌───────────────┐  │    │               │\n29: │                     │  │ControlPlane   │  │    │               │\n30: │                     │  │Client (WM)    │  │    │               │\n31: │                     │  └───────────────┘  │    │               │\n32: │                     │  ┌───────────────┐  │    │               │\n33: │                     │  │DataPlane      │  │    │               │\n34: │                     │  │Client (Router)│  │    │               │\n35: │                     │  └───────────────┘  │    │               │\n36: │                     └─────────────────────┘    │               │\n37: └────────────────────────────────────────────────┼───────────────┘\n38:                                                  │\n39: ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────┼───────────────┐\n40: │                  AgentCube Infrastructure      │               │\n41: │  ┌──────────────────┐    ┌────────────────────┼──────────┐    │\n42: │  │ Workload Manager │◀───│ Control Plane API  │          │    │\n43: │  │ (session mgmt)   │    │ /v1/code-interpreter│          │    │\n44: │  └────────┬─────────┘    └────────────────────┘          │    │\n45: │           │                                               │    │\n46: │  ┌────────▼─────────┐    ┌────────────────────────────┐  │    │\n47: │  │   Router         │◀───│ Data Plane API             │  │    │\n48: │  │   (session route)│    │ /v1/namespaces/{ns}/       │  │    │\n49: │  └────────┬─────────┘    │  code-interpreters/{cr}/   │  │    │\n50: │           │              │  invocations/api/*         │  │    │\n51: │  ┌────────▼─────────┐    └────────────────────────────┘  │    │\n52: │  │  Sandbox Pod     │                                     │    │\n53: │  │  (code exec)     │                                     │    │\n54: │  └──────────────────┘                                     │    │\n55: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n56: ```\n57: \n58: ## Dify Plugin — File Map\n59: \n60: | File | Role |\n61: |------|------|\n62: | `main.py` | `Plugin(DifyPluginEnv(MAX_REQUEST_TIMEOUT=120)).run()` |\n63: | `manifest.yaml` | Root plugin manifest for Dify |\n64: | `provider/agentcube.yaml` | Tool provider identity + tool list + Python entry |\n65: | `provider/agentcube.py` | `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider` |\n66: | `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml` | Tool parameter schema |\n67: | `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py` | `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool` |\n68: | `requirements.txt` | `dify-plugin` + `agentcube-sdk` pins |\n69: | `GUIDE.md`, `README.md`, `PRIVACY.md`, `.difyignore` | Docs / packaging |\n70: \n71: ## `manifest.yaml` Structure (Exact Top-Level Keys)\n72: \n73: From source:\n74: \n75: - `version`: `0.0.2`\n76: - `type`: `plugin`\n77: - `author`: `volcano-sh`\n78: - `name`: `agentcube`\n79: - `label`: map `en_US`, `ja_JP`, `zh_Hans`, `pt_BR` → `Agentcube`\n80: - `description`: multilingual strings (AgentCube description)\n81: - `icon`: `icon.png`\n82: - `icon_dark`: `icon-dark.png`\n83: - `resource`: `memory`, `permission` subtree (`tool`, `model`, `endpoint`, `app`, `storage` flags and sizes)\n84: - `plugins.tools`: list `[provider/agentcube.yaml]`\n85: - `meta`: `version`, `arch` (`amd64`, `arm64`), `runner` (`language: python`, `version: \"3.12\"`, `entrypoint: main`), `minimum_dify_version: null`\n86: - `created_at`, `privacy`, `repo`, `verified`\n87: \n88: ## `provider/agentcube.yaml` Structure\n89: \n90: - `identity`: `author`, `name`, `label` (multilingual), `description` (multilingual), `icon`\n91: - Commented `oauth_schema` block (not active)\n92: - `tools`: list `[tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml]`\n93: - `extra.python.source`: `provider/agentcube.py`\n94: \n95: ## Tool Definition (`tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml`)\n96: \n97: - `identity.name`: `agentcube-code-interpreter`\n98: - `identity.author`: `agentcube`\n99: - `identity.label` / `description` (human + llm strings)\n100: - `parameters` (each has `name`, `type`, `required`, `label`, `human_description`, `llm_description`, `form`):\n101: \n102: | name | type | required | form | notes |\n103: |------|------|----------|------|-------|\n104: | `router_url` | string | true | form | |\n105: | `workload_manager_url` | string | true | form | |\n106: | `language` | select | false | llm | options: `python`, `javascript`, `typescript` |\n107: | `code` | string | false | llm | |\n108: | `command` | string | false | llm | |\n109: | `session_id` | string | false | llm | |\n110: | `session_reuse` | boolean | false | llm | |\n111: | `code_interpreter_id` | string | false | llm | |\n112: \n113: - `extra.python.source`: `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py`\n114: \n115: ## Provider Implementation (`provider/agentcube.py`)\n116: \n117: ```python\n118: from dify_plugin import ToolProvider\n119: from dify_plugin.errors.tool import ToolProviderCredentialValidationError\n120: \n121: class AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider(ToolProvider):\n122:     def _validate_credentials(self, credentials: dict[str, Any]) -> None:\n123:         try:\n124:             \"\"\" IMPLEMENT YOUR VALIDATION HERE \"\"\"\n125:         except Exception as e:\n126:             raise ToolProviderCredentialValidationError(str(e))\n127: ```\n128: \n129: (OAuth helper methods are present only as comments.)\n130: \n131: ## Tool Implementation (`tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py`)\n132: \n133: ```python\n134: from collections.abc import Generator\n135: from typing import Any\n136: from dify_plugin import Tool\n137: from dify_plugin.entities.tool import ToolInvokeMessage\n138: from agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient\n139: \n140: class AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool(Tool):\n141:     def _invoke(self, tool_parameters: dict[str, Any]) -> Generator[ToolInvokeMessage]:\n142:         result = self.execute(**tool_parameters)\n143:         yield self.create_json_message(result)\n144: \n145:     def execute(\n146:         self,\n147:         router_url=None,\n148:         workload_manager_url=None,\n149:         language=\"python\",\n150:         code_interpreter_id=None,\n151:         session_id=None,\n152:         code=None,\n153:         command=None,\n154:         session_reuse=False,\n155:         **kwargs\n156:     ): ...\n157: ```\n158: \n159: ## Plugin Dependencies (`integrations/dify-plugin/requirements.txt`)\n160: \n161: ```\n162: dify-plugin>=0.4.2,<0.5.0\n163: agentcube-sdk>=0.0.10\n164: ```\n165: \n166: ## Data Structures\n167: \n168: ### Dify Plugin Tool Parameters\n169: \n170: ```python\n171: class ToolParameters(TypedDict, total=False):\n172:     router_url: str            # Required: Router endpoint URL\n173:     workload_manager_url: str  # Required: Workload Manager endpoint URL\n174:     language: str              # Optional: \"python\" | \"javascript\" | \"typescript\"\n175:     code: str                  # Optional: Source code to execute\n176:     command: str               # Optional: Shell command to execute\n177:     session_id: str            # Optional: Reuse existing session\n178:     session_reuse: bool        # Optional: Whether to reuse session\n179:     code_interpreter_id: str   # Optional: Interpreter identifier\n180: ```\n181: \n182: ### Execute Result\n183: \n184: ```python\n185: class ExecuteResult(TypedDict):\n186:     success: bool\n187:     output: str | None         # stdout or execution result\n188:     error: str | None          # stderr or error message\n189:     exit_code: int | None      # Process exit code\n190:     session_id: str | None     # Active session identifier\n191:     files: list[str] | None    # List of files in workspace\n192: ```\n193: \n194: ### PCAP Analyzer Response Model\n195: \n196: ```python\n197: class AnalyzeResponse(BaseModel):\n198:     script: str                          # Generated analysis script\n199:     results: list[dict[str, Any]]       # Execution results from sandbox\n200:     report: str                          # LLM-generated analysis report\n201: ```\n202: \n203: ### Sandbox Runner State\n204: \n205: ```python\n206: class SandboxRunnerState(Enum):\n207:     INITIALIZED = \"initialized\"\n208:     WARMING = \"warming\"\n209:     READY = \"ready\"\n210:     RUNNING = \"running\"\n211:     STOPPED = \"stopped\"\n212:     ERROR = \"error\"\n213: ```\n214: \n215: ## API Contracts\n216: \n217: ### Dify Plugin — Tool Invocation\n218: \n219: **Entry Point:** `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool._invoke(tool_parameters)`\n220: \n221: - **Input:** `dict[str, Any]` matching tool parameter schema\n222: - **Output:** `Generator[ToolInvokeMessage]` yielding `create_json_message(result)`\n223: - **Timeout:** 120 seconds (configured in `main.py`)\n224: \n225: **Execution Flow:**\n226: \n227: ```\n228: _invoke(tool_parameters)\n229:   └── execute(**tool_parameters)\n230:         ├── Create CodeInterpreterClient(router_url, workload_manager_url, ...)\n231:         ├── If session_reuse and session_id: reuse existing session\n232:         ├── If code: run_code(language, code)\n233:         ├── If command: execute_command(command)\n234:         ├── Collect result dict\n235:         └── Cleanup client (context manager or explicit stop)\n236: ```\n237: \n238: ### PCAP Analyzer — FastAPI Endpoints\n239: \n240: #### `POST /analyze`\n241: \n242: **Request:**\n243: \n244: | Field | Type | Required | Description |\n245: |-------|------|----------|-------------|\n246: | `pcap_file` | `UploadFile` | No | PCAP file upload (multipart) |\n247: | `pcap_path` | `str` (Form) | No | Path to PCAP file on server |\n248: \n249: **Response:** `AnalyzeResponse` (JSON)\n250: \n251: **Errors:**\n252: \n253: | Status | Condition |\n254: |--------|-----------|\n255: | 400 | Neither `pcap_file` nor `pcap_path` provided |\n256: | 422 | Invalid form data |\n257: | 500 | Analysis pipeline failure |\n258: \n259: #### Startup Hook\n260: \n261: ```python\n262: @app.on_event(\"startup\")\n263: async def on_startup():\n264:     # 1. Validate OPENAI_API_KEY is set\n265:     # 2. Build ChatOpenAI instance\n266:     # 3. Build PLANNER and REPORTER agents\n267:     # 4. Fail startup if API key missing\n268: ```\n269: \n270: ### AgentCube SDK — Control Plane API\n271: \n272: | Method | Path | Body | Response |\n273: |--------|------|------|----------|\n274: | `POST` | `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter` | `{\"name\", \"namespace\", \"ttl\", \"metadata\"}` | `{\"sessionId\": \"...\"}` |\n275: | `DELETE` | `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{session_id}` | — | 200/404 (both treated as success) |\n276: \n277: **Headers:**\n278: \n279: - `Content-Type: application/json`\n280: - `Authorization: Bearer {token}` (if token non-empty)\n281: \n282: **Timeouts:** `(connect_timeout=5.0, timeout=120)`\n283: \n284: ### AgentCube SDK — Data Plane API (Code Interpreter)\n285: \n286: Base URL: `urljoin(router_url, \"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/code-interpreters/{cr_name}/invocations/\")`\n287: \n288: | Method | Relative Path | Body | Notes |\n289: |--------|---------------|------|-------|\n290: | `POST` | `api/execute` | `{\"command\": [...], \"timeout\": \"<n>s\"}` | Read timeout = command_timeout + 2.0 |\n291: | `POST` | `api/files` | `{\"path\", \"content\" (base64), \"mode\": \"0644\"}` | Write file |\n292: | `POST` | `api/files` (multipart) | `files={'file': ...}`, `data={'path', 'mode'}` | Upload file |\n293: | `GET` | `api/files/{clean_path}` | — | `stream=True` for download |\n294: | `GET` | `api/files` | query `path` | List files |\n295: \n296: **Headers:**\n297: \n298: - `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}` (on all requests)\n299: - `Content-Type: application/json` (for JSON body requests)\n300: \n301: ### AgentCube SDK — Data Plane API (Agent Runtime)\n302: \n303: Base URL: `urljoin(router_url, \"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\")`\n304: \n305: | Method | Path | Headers | Body |\n306: |--------|------|---------|------|\n307: | `GET` | `{base_url}` | — | Bootstrap session (reads `x-agentcube-session-id` header) |\n308: | `POST` | `{base_url}` | `x-agentcube-session-id`, `Content-Type: application/json` | `json=payload` |\n309: \n310: ## Error Handling\n311: \n312: ### Exception Hierarchy\n313: \n314: ```\n315: Exception\n316: ├── AgentCubeError (base for all AgentCube SDK errors)\n317: │   ├── CommandExecutionError\n318: │   │   ├── exit_code: int\n319: │   │   ├── stderr: str\n320: │   │   └── command: str | None\n321: │   ├── SessionError\n322: │   └── DataPlaneError\n323: ├── ValueError (configuration errors)\n324: └── requests.RequestException (HTTP errors)\n325: ```\n326: \n327: ### Error Scenarios and Handling\n328: \n329: | Scenario | Exception | Handling Strategy |\n330: |----------|-----------|-------------------|\n331: | Missing `router_url` | `ValueError` | Raised in `CodeInterpreterClient.__init__` |\n332: | Session creation failure | `SessionError` / `ValueError` | Logged, cleanup attempted, re-raised |\n333: | Data plane init failure after session create | Any | Log warning, `delete_session()`, set `session_id=None`, re-raise |\n334: | Command non-zero exit | `CommandExecutionError` | Raised with `exit_code`, `stderr`, `command` |\n335: | HTTP request failure | `requests.RequestException` | Propagated to caller |\n336: | Missing API key at startup | `ValueError` / `SystemExit` | FastAPI startup hook fails, process exits |\n337: | Invalid Dify credentials | `ToolProviderCredentialValidationError` | Surface to Dify platform |\n338: | PCAP file not provided | `HTTPException(400)` | Return 400 with error message |\n339: | Analysis retry exhausted | `HTTPException(500)` | Return partial results with error |\n340: \n341: ### Dify Plugin Error Propagation\n342: \n343: ```python\n344: def _validate_credentials(self, credentials: dict[str, Any]) -> None:\n345:     try:\n346:         # Validation logic (e.g., test connection to endpoints)\n347:         pass\n348:     except Exception as e:\n349:         raise ToolProviderCredentialValidationError(str(e))\n350: ```\n351: \n352: ### PCAP Analyzer Retry Logic\n353: \n354: ```python\n355: def _analyze_with_retries(\n356:     planner, reporter, runner, pcap_local_path, max_retries: int = 2\n357: ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n358:     script = _plan_script(planner, pcap_local_path)\n359:     for attempt in range(max_retries + 1):\n360:         try:\n361:             results = _execute_once_in_runner(runner, pcap_local_path, script)\n362:             break\n363:         except CommandExecutionError:\n364:             if attempt == max_retries:\n365:                 raise\n366:             script = _repair_script(planner, script, results)\n367:     report = _report(reporter, results)\n368:     return {\"script\": script, \"results\": results, \"report\": report}\n369: ```\n370: \n371: ## Testing Strategy\n372: \n373: ### Unit Tests\n374: \n375: | Component | Test Cases |\n376: |-----------|------------|\n377: | `ControlPlaneClient` | Session create/delete success, 404 handling, auth token resolution, URL fallback to env |\n378: | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` | Execute command, file write/upload/download/list, session header presence, timeout buffer |\n379: | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` | Bootstrap session id, invoke with payload, missing session header error |\n380: | `CodeInterpreterClient` | Context manager lifecycle, data plane init failure cleanup, router URL required validation |\n381: | `AgentRuntimeClient` | Context manager, invoke without session error, bootstrap session |\n382: | Dify Tool (`AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool`) | `_invoke` yields JSON message, `execute` delegates to SDK client |\n383: | Dify Provider (`AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider`) | `_validate_credentials` raises on error, passes on success |\n384: | `SandboxRunner` | Upload file/bytes, run command, stop, warmup delay |\n385: \n386: ### Integration Tests\n387: \n388: | Scenario | Setup | Assertions |\n389: |----------|-------|------------|\n390: | End-to-end code execution | Mock Router + Workload Manager | Code runs, output returned, session cleaned up |\n391: | PCAP analysis pipeline | Mock LLM + SandboxRunner | Script planned, executed, report generated |\n392: | Dify plugin invocation | Mock Dify framework | Tool invoked, result returned as JSON |\n393: | FastAPI `/analyze` endpoint | TestClient with mock agents | 200 with valid `AnalyzeResponse` |\n394: | Missing API key startup | Unset `OPENAI_API_KEY` | Startup fails |\n395: \n396: ### Test Fixtures\n397: \n398: ```python\n399: @pytest.fixture\n400: def mock_control_plane():\n401:     \"\"\"Mock Workload Manager responses for session create/delete.\"\"\"\n402:     with responses.RequestsMock() as rsps:\n403:         rsps.add(\n404:             responses.POST,\n405:             re.compile(r\".*/v1/code-interpreter$\"),\n406:             json={\"sessionId\": \"test-session-123\"},\n407:             status=200,\n408:         )\n409:         yield rsps\n410: \n411: @pytest.fixture\n412: def mock_data_plane():\n413:     \"\"\"Mock Router data plane responses.\"\"\"\n414:     with responses.RequestsMock() as rsps:\n415:         rsps.add(\n416:             responses.POST,\n417:             re.compile(r\".*/api/execute$\"),\n418:             json={\"exit_code\": 0, \"stdout\": \"hello\", \"stderr\": \"\"},\n419:             status=200,\n420:         )\n421:         yield rsps\n422: \n423: @pytest.fixture\n424: def sandbox_runner():\n425:     \"\"\"SandboxRunner with mocked CodeInterpreterClient.\"\"\"\n426:     runner = SandboxRunner(name=\"test-interpreter\", namespace=\"test\", warmup_sec=0)\n427:     runner.client = MagicMock()\n428:     return runner\n429: ```\n430: \n431: ### Test File Layout\n432: \n433: ```\n434: integrations/\n435: ├── dify-plugin/\n436: │   ├── tests/\n437: │   │   ├── test_provider.py\n438: │   │   ├── test_tool.py\n439: │   │   └── test_manifest.py\n440: │   └── requirements.txt\n441: ├── example/pcap-analyzer/\n442: │   ├── tests/\n443: │   │   ├── test_pcap_analyzer.py\n444: │   │   ├── test_sandbox_runner.py\n445: │   │   └── test_agents.py\n446: │   └── requirements.txt\n447: ```\n448: \n449: ## PCAP Analyzer — Application Structure (`example/pcap-analyzer/`)\n450: \n451: | File | Role |\n452: |------|------|\n453: | `pcap_analyzer.py` | FastAPI app, agents, sandbox runner, analysis orchestration, `uvicorn` entry |\n454: | `requirements.txt` | FastAPI, uvicorn, LangChain / LangGraph stack, multipart, etc. |\n455: | `Dockerfile` | `uv` base image, installs reqs, copies `sdk-python/agentcube` + `pcap_analyzer.py` |\n456: | `deployment.yaml` | K8s Deployment + env for OpenAI-compatible API and AgentCube URLs |\n457: | `README.md` | Documentation |\n458: \n459: ## FastAPI Application (`pcap_analyzer.py`)\n460: \n461: ### Globals / Config (Selected)\n462: \n463: | Name | Source | Default / Value |\n464: |------|--------|-----------------|\n465: | `API_KEY` | `OPENAI_API_KEY` | Required at startup |\n466: | `API_BASE_URL` | `OPENAI_API_BASE` | `https://api.siliconflow.cn/v1` |\n467: | `MODEL_NAME` | `OPENAI_MODEL` | `Qwen/QwQ-32B` |\n468: | `CODEINTERPRETER_NAME` | env | `my-interpreter` |\n469: | `SANDBOX_NAMESPACE` | env | `default` |\n470: | `SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC` | env | `5` |\n471: | `SERVER_HOST` | constant | `0.0.0.0` |\n472: | `SERVER_PORT` | constant | `8000` |\n473: | `SERVER_RELOAD` | constant | `True` |\n474: \n475: ### Core Classes / Functions\n476: \n477: ```python\n478: class SandboxRunner:\n479:     def __init__(self, name: str = \"my-interpreter\", namespace: str = \"default\", warmup_sec: int = 5): ...\n480:     def upload_file(self, local_path: str, remote_path: str) -> bool: ...\n481:     def upload_bytes(self, data: bytes, remote_path: str) -> bool: ...\n482:     def run(self, command: str) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n483:     def stop(self): ...\n484: \n485: def build_react_agent(llm, system_prompt: str): ...\n486: def invoke_react_agent(agent, user_text: str) -> str: ...\n487: def build_planner_agent(llm): ...\n488: def build_reporter_agent(llm): ...\n489: \n490: def _plan_script(agent, pcap_local_path: str) -> str: ...\n491: def _repair_script(agent, prev_script: str, results: List[Dict[str, Any]]) -> str: ...\n492: def _execute_once_in_runner(runner: SandboxRunner, pcap_local_path: str, script: str) -> List[Dict[str, Any]]: ...\n493: def _analyze_with_retries(..., max_retries: int = 2) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n494: def _report(agent, results: List[Dict[str, Any]]) -> str: ...\n495: \n496: class AnalyzeResponse(BaseModel):\n497:     script: str\n498:     results: List[Dict[str, Any]]\n499:     report: str\n500: \n501: app = FastAPI(title=\"PCAP Analyzer — Env-Only Config\")\n502: ```\n503: \n504: ### FastAPI Endpoints\n505: \n506: | Method | Path | Signature / Behavior |\n507: |--------|------|----------------------|\n508: | (event) | startup | `on_startup()` → builds `ChatOpenAI`, `PLANNER`, `REPORTER`; fails if no API key |\n509: | `POST` | `/analyze` | `async def analyze_endpoint(pcap_file: UploadFile = File(None), pcap_path: str = Form(None))` → `response_model=AnalyzeResponse` |\n510: \n511: ### Imports of Note\n512: \n513: ```python\n514: from fastapi import FastAPI, UploadFile, File, Form, HTTPException\n515: from pydantic import BaseModel\n516: import uvicorn\n517: from langchain_openai import ChatOpenAI\n518: from langgraph.prebuilt import create_react_agent\n519: from langchain_core.messages import HumanMessage, AIMessage\n520: from agentcube.code_interpreter import CodeInterpreterClient\n521: from agentcube.exceptions import CommandExecutionError\n522: ```\n523: \n524: ## Kubernetes Deployment (`deployment.yaml`)\n525: \n526: - `Deployment` `pcap-analyzer` in `namespace: default`\n527: - Container `pcap-analyzer`, image `pcap-analyzer:latest`, `imagePullPolicy: IfNotPresent`\n528: - Container port `8000` TCP\n529: - Resources: requests `cpu: 200m`, `memory: 100Mi`; limits `cpu: 1`, `memory: 1Gi`\n530: - Env: `OPENAI_API_KEY` from secret `pcap-analyzer-secrets` key `openai-api-key`; `OPENAI_API_BASE`, `OPENAI_MODEL`, `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`, `ROUTER_URL`, `CODEINTERPRETER_NAME`, `SANDBOX_NAMESPACE`, `SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC`\n531: - Command: `[\"uv\"]`, args: `[\"run\", \"pcap_analyzer.py\"]`\n532: \n533: ## Dockerfile Highlights\n534: \n535: - Base: `ghcr.io/astral-sh/uv:python3.12-bookworm-slim`\n536: - `uv venv` + `uv pip install -r requirements.txt`\n537: - Copies `sdk-python/agentcube` → `./agentcube/`, `pcap_analyzer.py` → `./`\n538: - `ENV PYTHONPATH=\"/app\"`, exposes `8000`\n539: - `CMD [\"uv\", \"run\", \"pcap_analyzer.py\"]`\n540: \n541: ## PCAP Example Python Dependencies (`example/pcap-analyzer/requirements.txt`)\n542: \n543: Pinned packages include: `fastapi==0.120.0`, `uvicorn==0.38.0`, `langchain==1.0.2`, `langchain-classic==1.0.0`, `langchain-community==0.4.1`, `langchain-core==1.0.1`, `langchain-openai==1.0.1`, `langchain-text-splitters==1.0.0`, `langgraph==1.0.1`, `langgraph-checkpoint==3.0.0`, `langgraph-prebuilt==1.0.1`, `langgraph-sdk==0.2.9`, `langsmith==0.4.38`, `paramiko==4.0.0`, `python-multipart==0.0.20`\n544: \n545: *(The Dockerfile vendors `agentcube` from the monorepo copy; it is not listed in this `requirements.txt`.)*\n\n(End of file - total 545 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube Integrations — Design\n\nSources: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/integrations/dify-plugin/`, `/tmp/agentcube-ref/example/pcap-analyzer/`.\n\n## Architecture Overview\n\nThe integrations module bridges AgentCube with two external systems:\n\n1. **Dify Plugin** — A Dify-compatible Python plugin that exposes AgentCube's Code Interpreter as a tool within the Dify AI application platform.\n2. **PCAP Analyzer** — A standalone FastAPI service that demonstrates end-to-end usage of the AgentCube SDK for PCAP file analysis via LLM-planned sandbox execution.\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                        Dify Platform                            │\n│  ┌──────────────┐   ┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐ │\n│  │  Dify Agent  │──▶│  AgentCube Dify Plugin                  │ │\n│  │  (LLM)       │   │  ┌───────────┐  ┌─────────────────────┐ │ │\n│  └──────────────┘   │  │ Provider  │─▶│ Tool: Code          │ │ │\n│                     │  │ (creds)   │  │ Interpreter         │ │ │\n│                     │  └───────────┘  └─────────┬───────────┘ │ │","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/integrations/design.md","time":{"start":1775883011077,"end":1775883011091}}}}
